Site description: Freya Glacier is one of the very few direct mass balance observation sites amongst Greenland’s peripheral glaciers. Seasonal mass balance observations started in 2007, the automatic weather station (AWS) on the glacier surface (a PROMICE setup) is running since 2016. The AWS is operated by Geosphere Austria in close cooperation with University of Graz and GEUS.
Predominant surface cover: Permanent snow and ice(Surface cover types (GlobCover2009))

The Jamtalferner glacier is amongst the longest mass balance time series in Austria, and the records are complemented by more than 100 years of glacier fluctuations records and the availability of early maps. Additional research is carried out under the umbrella of the environmental education institution Jamtalferner, e.g. investigating periglacial succession. This site is also a LTER/LTSER site.
